b'' b'there is a new version of the rtrace ray-tracing package at' b'asterix.inescn.pt in directory pub/rtrace.' b'check the readme file.' b'' b'rtrace now can use the suit toolkit to have a nice user interface.' b'compile it with -dsuit or modify the makefile.' b'i have binaries of rtrace with suit for sun sparc, sgi indigo' b'and dos/go32.' b'please contact me if interested.' b'' b'****************************************' b'' b'the mac rtrace port is in directory pub/rtrace/macintosh' b'' b'****************************************' b'' b'small changes were done since version mainly:' b'' b'1. now it is possible to discard backface polygons and triangles' b'for fast preview...' b'' b'2. the support program scn2sff has been reworked to use temp files.' b'' b'****************************************' b'' b'here goes a short description of current converters from' b'cad/molecular/chemistry packages to the scn format.' b'' b'the package programs are related as below (those marked with have been' b'modified)' b'' b'irit2scn' b'irit b'| nff (nffclean, nffp2pp)' b'sol2scn b'acad11 nff2sff' b'| b'mol2scn\t v scn2sff* v\trtrace*' b'alchemy scn sff pic or ppm' b'^ cpp b'pdb2scn picmix' b'pdb picblend' b'| ppmmix*' b'chem2scn ppmblend*' b'chemical b'|' b'3ds2scn* b'3d studio b'|' b'iv2scn* b'iris inventor b'' b'****************************************' b'' b'the dos port of rtrace is in pub/rtrace/pc-386 (rtrac820.arj,' b'utils820.arj and image820.arj). see the readme file there.' b'requires djgpp go32 dos extender (version included), which can be' b'found in directory pub/pc/djgpp (and in many sites around netland).' b'there are also demo scenes, manuals and all the source code...' b'' b'****************************************' b'' b'please feel free to get it and use it.' b'hope you like it.' b'' b'regards,' b'antonio costa.' b'.........................................................................' b'o o' b'/ i n e s c' b'| o b'| o comp. graphics cad decnet porto::acos